<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="absorb-vt">absorb <strong><em>vt</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /əbˈsɔːb/    美 /əbˈsɔːrb/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>吸收</strong></h4>
<p>to take in and hold sth (a liquid, heat, etc.)：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A transparent object doesn’t absorb light.
透明的物体不吸收光。</p><footer>2015 北京改</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>One hectare of forest can absorb 23 tons of carbon dioxide per year
一公顷森林每年可以吸收23吨二氧化碳。</p><footer>人教⑥ – 4</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>吸纳</strong></h4>
<p>to take sth into sth larger, so that it becomes part of it：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Service work absorbed a great number of women who arrived in the cities from the country.
服务业吸纳了很多从农村来到城市的妇女。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>理解；掌握</strong></h4>
<p>to take sth into the mind and understand it(take in)：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>absorb new knowledge / information
掌握新知识/新信息</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’ve just been so busy studying and trying to absorb all the new things around me.
我一直忙于学习，并试图理解身边所有的新事物。</p><footer>北师大④ – 12</footer></div>

<h4 id="4">4.<strong>吸引；使专心</strong></h4>
<p>to interest sb so much that they don’t pay attention to other things：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>This work has absorbed him for years.
多年来他一直专注于这项工作。</p></div>

<h4 id="5">5.<strong>缓冲：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Well-designed sports shoes should absorb the impact on your feet.
设计精良的运动鞋可以缓解脚部受到的冲击。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>absorbed /əb'sɔːbd/ adj   </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When something did interest me, I could become absorbed.
当某件事确实让我感兴趣时，我就能够全神贯注。</p><footer>2016 北京</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>( be ) absorbed in:</strong>
</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When deeply absorbed in work, he always forgets all about eating or sleeping.
他专注工作时，总是废寝忘食。</p><footer>2012 北京改</footer></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li><strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (absorb) in painting, John didn’t notice evening approaching.  （2015 天津改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. Absorbed  </p></div>